  "body": "I run a geth instance on AWS. Blockchain fully sync, works perfectly.\r\nAWS SIDE: Security group is ok: allow inbound requests from everywhere / every ports \r\n\r\nFrom my local machine, i want to attach a Javascript console to that AWS geth instance. I got this error i ccannot solve \r\n\r\n\"Fatal: Unable to attach to remote geth: dial tcp <ip of my instance> connectex: No connection could be made because the target machine actively refused it.\"\r\n\r\nI think i tried everything in the geth config:\r\n\r\n- AWS SIDE: --ws --wsport 8546 --wsorigins=\"*\" ; LOCAL SIDE: geth attach  ws://<aws instance pub ip>:8546\r\n- AWS SIDE: --http --http.port 8545 --http.corsdomain '*' ; LOCAL SIDE: geth attach  http://<aws instance pub ip>:8545\r\n\r\nI desactivated my local windows firewall, linux server firewall is inactive...\r\n\r\nI can attach with ipc ON AWS SERVER via ssh without any problem. \r\nBut as i have some code to test, i want to be able to do quick changes to my code on my local machine and test it by dialing geth on aws via http or ws. \r\n\r\nAnyone can save my day? \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
